This product uses software developed as part of:
* Lua <https://www.lua.org> - Lua language implementation, the only required dependency.
* Catch2 <https://github.com/catchorg/Catch2> - used for unit tests. Optional, enabled by default.
* lua-compat-5.3 <https://github.com/keplerproject/lua-compat-5.3> - some compatibility code is borrowed from Kepler Project. Integrated into project source.
* Google Benchmark <https://github.com/google/benchmark> - used for microbenchmarks. Optional, disabled by default.
* Sol2 <https://github.com/ThePhD/sol2> - used for microbenchmarks as LuaCppB competitor. Optional, disabled by default.
